The paper deals with algorithms for estimating the volume of convex bodies and integrating Gaussian distributions over convex sets, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of a membership oracle suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS), while the improved algorithm for sampling a Gaussian distribution may be of interest to researchers in information theory (cs.IT) and control theory (cs.SY).
